{
  "text": "\u2022 Death of hippocampal neurons: The neurophysiological mechanisms of memory are presently ill-understood, but one thing that is known for sure is that a properly functioning hippocampus is essential for the laying down of new memories. Hence the demonstrated loss of hippocampal neurons in teenaged rats exposed to RF [CITATION_1] reinforces the warning at the end of the preceding subsection.",
  "correct_citation": {
